column17: Parents do not need to worry if their child misbehaves a lot.
column18: Too much affection, such as hugging and kissing, can make a child weak.
column19: It is good to let children explore and experiment.
column20: It is very important that there are consequences when a child breaks a rule, big or small.
column21: Parents can prepare young children to succeed in school by teaching them things, such as shapes and numbers.
column22: It is okay if young children boss around their caregivers.
column23: It’s important for parents to help children learn to deal with their emotions.
column24: A child who has close bonds with his or her parents will have better relationships later on in life.
column25: Parents can help babies learn language by talking to them.
column26: Children don’t need to learn about numbers and math until they go to school.
column27: Parents should not try to calm a child who is upset, it is better to let children calm themselves.
column28: Children and parents do not need to feel emotionally close as long as children are kept safe.
column29: Reading books to children is not helpful if they have not yet learned to speak.
column30: It is not helpful to explain the reasons for rules to young children because they won’t understand.
column31: It is very important that children learn to respect adults, such as parents and teachers.
column32: Children should be comforted when they are scared or unhappy.
column33: Young children should be allowed to make their own decisions, like what to play with and when to eat.
column34: It is okay if children see adults as equals rather than viewing them with respect.
column35: Children who receive too much attention from their parents become spoiled.
column36: Children should be grateful to their parents.
column37: Babies can learn a lot just by playing.
column38: Babies can’t learn about the world until they learn to speak.
column39: It is very important for young children to do as they are told, for example, waiting when they are told to wait.
column40: Parents should pay attention to what their child likes and dislikes.
